@page "/"

<PageTitle>QuickGrid.Toolkit samples</PageTitle>

<h1>QuickGrid.Toolkit</h1>

<p class="lead">
    Extensions for the Blazor
    <a href="https://aspnet.github.io/quickgridsamples/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">QuickGrid</a>:
    runtime, data-driven column management with a show/hide UI, custom column types, quick search and footer totals.
</p>

<p>
    Define your columns once in a <code>ColumnManager&lt;T&gt;</code>, then render them through a plain
    <code>QuickGrid</code> or the all-in-one <code>QuickGridWrapper</code>. The same configuration can drive
    several grids that each expose a different set of visible columns.
</p>

<h2>Examples</h2>

<p>Each example below shares the same column setup and links to the next, so they read as a progression.</p>

<div class="list-group mb-4">
    <a class="list-group-item list-group-item-action" href="users-grid">
        <strong>QuickGrid + ColumnManager</strong>
        <div class="small text-muted">
            Write your own <code>&lt;QuickGrid&gt;</code> and render columns from a <code>ColumnManager</code>,
            with a <code>ColumnSelector</code> for show/hide. The low-level building blocks.
        </div>
    </a>
    <a class="list-group-item list-group-item-action" href="users-grid-wrapper">
        <strong>QuickGridWrapper</strong>
        <div class="small text-muted">
            The same columns inside one component that adds a toolbar, quick search and pagination.
        </div>
    </a>
    <a class="list-group-item list-group-item-action" href="total-footer-example">
        <strong>Total Footer</strong>
        <div class="small text-muted">
            Add an automatic, summed totals row to a <code>QuickGridWrapper</code>.
        </div>
    </a>
</div>

<p>
    Source and documentation on
    <a href="https://github.com/VaclavElias/QuickGrid.Toolkit" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>.
</p>